data.title: Production on Channing Tatum, Mila Kunis Movie Continues Near Plainfield
data.meta_description: Production on Channing Tatum, Mila Kunis Movie Continues Near Plainfield - Plainfield, IL - A Patch reader snapped these photos of extras on the set of the sci-fi film.
data.text:
A Patch reader snapped these photos of extras on the set of the sci-fi film.

A bit of Hollywood came to Plainfield this week as the 2014 release "Jupiter Ascending" began filming at a farmhouse in Minooka, using District 202's Aux Sable Middle School as a home base for the cast and crew.

Sign up for the Plainfield Patch newsletter

Like Plainfield Patch on Facebook and follow us on Twitter

Fans caught glimpses of stars Channing Tatum and Mila Kunis, who even took time out to greet onlookers outside of Aux Sable.

Read: Fans Meet Mila Kunis Outside Aux Sable Middle School

On Sunday, Plainfield Patch reader Ashley Reitz shared some photos of extras getting ready to film scenes near Aux Sable, as well as helicopters that landed nearby.

Reitz said the crew was filming scenes around 5 p.m. Sunday, although Tatum and Kunis were not part of the action.

Another star, however, was spotted near Plainfield Sunday. Sue Zarbock shared a photo of "Game of Thrones" and "Lord of the Rings" actor Sean Bean greeting fans on Plainfield Patch's Facebook page. Bean co-stars with Tatum and Kunis in "Jupiter Ascending."

According to the Kendall County Sheriff's Department, the filming is scheduled to be on site through Aug. 6.

IMDb.com describes the movie this way: "In a universe where humans are near the bottom of the evolutionary ladder, a young destitute human woman is targeted for assassination by the Queen of the Universe because her very existence threatens to end the Queen's reign."
